The %office_hours field will be used to contain the formatting settings
        of each %timeslot field. You may add 1 to 7 %timeslot fields,
        one for each weekday.

The %season field is optional and is used as a table column to also display seasonal %office_hours and Exception dates to the table rows. Season labels cannot be influenced. Exceptions can be removed and formatted, also using the %office_hours field settings, section Exception days.
The Office Hours module provides a "weekly office hours" field type. It allows to add a field to any Content type, in order to display when a location is open or closed on a weekly basis.
The days to show in the formatter. Useful in combination with the Current Status block.

The maximum number of time slots, that are allowed per day.
Warning! Lowering this setting after data has been created could result in the loss of data!
Be careful when using more then 2 slots per day, since not all external services (like Google Places) support this.

The normal weekday time slots will be replaced
        with time slots from an exception date, if any exists.
        This will generate a 'rolling' calendar for the regular week
        (On Wednesday, the next tuesday will be replaced,
        not the previous tuesday). Seasonal weeks are not affected.
The weekdays for this column. Create a column for each weekday.
This is fixed, by this field's nature.

This is unlimited by this field's nature.
